{"step_index":134,"source":"MODEL","type":"PLANNER_RESPONSE","status":"DONE","created_at":"2026-06-13T03:23:09Z","content":"I have fixed the issues causing the hydration errors and the 404 image missing error!\n\nHere is what was resolved:\n1. **Hydration Mismatch Fix:** The error you encountered (`<html lang=\"en\" - className=\"w-mod-ix lenis\">`) was caused because the imported Webflow and Lenis scripts mutate the `<html>` and `<body>` tags (by adding their own CSS classes like `w-mod-ix` and `lenis`) as soon as the client loads. This causes a mismatch with what Next.js rendered on the server. I added the `suppressHydrationWarning` prop to your `<html>`, `<body>`, and navigation `<a>` tags in `layout.tsx` so Next.js knows to ignore these specific attribute changes.\n2. **Missing Image 404:** The 404 error for `/images/arena-preview.png` occurred because the `arena-preview.png` file didn't exist, which we used to replace the freelancer portfolio slider earlier. I used the AI image generator tool to create a sleek, premium, glassmorphic UI mockup of the CodeDuel Arena and saved it directly to your `public/images/` directory.\n\n<truncated 429 bytes>"}
