{"step_index":320,"source":"MODEL","type":"PLANNER_RESPONSE","status":"DONE","created_at":"2026-06-13T03:48:05Z","content":"Ah! I see exactly what happened in the screenshot. \n\nWhen I added the `invert(0.9)` CSS filter and `mix-blend-mode` to make the orb glow, it accidentally inverted the background of the 3D canvas as well. This turned the entire right side of the screen into a bright white block, making the white text completely invisible!\n\nI have just pushed a fix to remove the `invert` and `mix-blend-mode` properties. Instead, I am now strictly using a combination of `hue-rotate(240deg)`, `saturate(3)`, and a custom purple `drop-shadow`. \n\nThis correctly forces the orb's glowing eyes and metallic reflections to shift into a vibrant purple/pink color **without** ruining the canvas background! I also darkened the main radial-gradient background so that the glassmorphism contrast is much higher and everything looks incredibly premium and readable.\n\nRefresh `http://localhost:3000` — the layout should now be perfectly visible again, retaining the dark aesthetic with a uniquely purple glowing 3D orb!"}
