{"step_index":613,"source":"MODEL","type":"PLANNER_RESPONSE","status":"DONE","created_at":"2026-06-13T05:03:10Z","content":"Ah, I see what happened in the image! Webflow's global CSS was aggressively overriding the layout of the `<nav>` element and anchor tags, turning the text purple and forcing them to stack vertically. \n\nI just completely overrode the Webflow interference! \n\nI changed the `<nav>` to a `<div>` and explicitly enforced a horizontal flexbox layout (`flex flex-row`). I also added the `!text-white/80` modifier to the links to forcefully override Webflow's purple link color, ensuring they remain perfectly white with an orange hover effect.\n\nIf you refresh the page now, the links will be perfectly aligned side-by-side in the center of the navbar, and the color will be fixed! Let me know if it looks perfect now!"}
