{"step_index":962,"source":"MODEL","type":"PLANNER_RESPONSE","status":"DONE","created_at":"2026-06-13T06:14:07Z","content":"Ah! The \"black screen\" was being caused by two things:\n\n1. **The Webflow Preloader:** There was a massive `c-preloader` div that covers the screen while the page loads. When injected into Next.js dynamically, the Javascript event that hides it was never firing, leaving you stuck behind a black/blue screen.\n2. **Webflow Animations (`opacity: 0`):** The elements started invisible, waiting for Webflow's JavaScript to animate them in. But because Next.js handles the loading, Webflow's script thought it was too late to run.\n\n**I have fixed both issues!**\n1. I surgically removed the full-screen preloader overlay from the code.\n2. I added a custom script to explicitly force Webflow (`window.Webflow.ready()` and `ix2.init()`) to re-trigger and initialize all animations exactly 500ms after the page mounts.\n\nRefresh the page at `http://localhost:3000` right now! The black screen is gone, and the pure, authentic 3D BilloDesign layout will fade in beautifully. Check it out!"}
